News_Title: Pakistani soldier hitting woman in Lahore
News_Text: A photo that appears to show a soldier about to beat a woman with his rifle has been shared in multiple social media posts that falsely claim it was taken during clashes between police and supporters of Imran Khan outside the former Pakistani prime ministers residence in the Zaman Park suburb in Lahore in March 2023. Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video recirculated to falsely claim ex-Pakistan president named journalists killers
News_Text: A video of former Pakistani president Asif Ali Zardari giving a press conference has been viewed tens of thousands of times in multiple Facebook posts with the false claim that he mentioned the names of the killers of a Pakistani journalist who was shot dead by police in Kenya in October 2022. The original video was in fact broadcast live in May 2022 which predates the journalists killing by several months.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo from 2013 Karachi protest falsely linked to Peshawar suicide bombing
News_Text: An image of a woman giving bangles to security forces has been shared thousands of times in social media posts that falsely claim it was taken after a deadly mosque blast in Pakistans Peshawar in January 2023. But the photo has been shared online since 2013 after a Karachi protest against alleged vote rigging in the election that year.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan politicians falsely claim foreign minister advocated making rich richer
News_Text: A video of Pakistans foreign minister has been shared by opposition politicians falsely claiming it shows him calling to make the rich richer at a time when an economic crisis gripped the country. However Bilawal Bhutto Zardari was in fact criticising the idea that everyone benefits from policies that boost the wealth of the countrys richest people.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Imran Khan supporters share old photo in posts about Pakistan rally arrests
News_Text: After clashes erupted between police and supporters of Pakistans ousted leader Imran Khan at a rally in Lahore in March 2023 a photo was shared in posts falsely claiming it showed officers forcing pro-Khan protesters to lie on the ground. However the photo actually shows police arresting members of a local crime network in Rawalpindi in May 2022.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo of Imran Khan-led rally in 2014 doctored to add gun
News_Text: A doctored photo that appears to show a man pointing a gun from a vehicle has been shared thousands of times in posts that falsely claim it shows a supporter of former Pakistan prime minister Imran Khan at an election rally in March 2023. It circulated online after local media reported that Khan had suspended an election rally in Lahore Pakistans second-largest city following arrests of his supporters. The weapon shown in the photo has been digitally inserted into an image from a rally that Khan led in August 2014.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo shows volunteers posing for artwork in Germany not captured Pakistani soldiers
News_Text: An image of dozens of naked people bent over has circulated in social media posts that falsely claim it shows Pakistani soldiers who were captured in 1971 during a nine-month war that saw then-East Pakistan emerge as an independent Bangladesh. The picture includes text that says it shows 93000 captured Pakistani army officers. The image in fact shows volunteers posing for a US photographer in Germany in 2006 when he created a sculpture for an art museum.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo of US gun control demonstration in 2018 falsely shared as rally for Pakistans Imran Khan
News_Text: After Pakistans former prime minister Imran Khan defied attempts to arrest him in March 2023 a photo of a huge crowd was shared by pro-Khan social media accounts that falsely claimed it showed supporters gathered outside his house. The picture was actually taken five years earlier at a demonstration in Washington DC calling for tougher gun laws.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Aide to Pakistans ex-PM Khan shares wrong photo in tweet about arrest attempt
News_Text: A photo of crowds packed onto a street has surfaced in social media posts that falsely claim it shows the chaotic scene outside the home of Pakistans ex-prime minister Imran Khan where supporters fought off police trying to arrest him. The photo was actually taken at Lahore High Court weeks before the clashes when Khan supporters gathered as the ex-leader appeared seeking protective bail.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo of tear gas shells falsely linked to Imran Khan clashes
News_Text: A photo has been shared hundreds of times in Facebook and Twitter posts that falsely claim it shows a pile of empty tear gas canisters after Pakistani police used them against supporters of former prime minister Imran Khan when they came to arrest him at his Lahore home on March 14. Although officers did use tear gas that day a reverse image search on Google shows the photo is from a November 2020 anti-blasphemy protest in Islamabad.
Label: Fake

News_Text: The Ministry of Finance on Saturday rejected the reports claiming that the federal government issued instructions to stop payment of pay and pensions saying all such rumours are completely false.The clarification comes after a local English daily reported that the Accountant General of Pakistan Revenue (AGPR) was directed by the finance ministry to stop clearing all the bill of the “federal ministries/divisions and attached departments till further orders”.

News_Title: Pakistan did not win the World Cup of Polo Championship 2022
News_Text: Pakistan won the World Polo Championship 2022 by beating Mexico in the Final 11-8 Spain won the World Polo Championship 2022. The Pakistan team defeated Mexico in a match 11-8 placing it in 5th position in the world cup rankings.
Label: Fake

News_Title: AC Karor Lal Esan’s letter regarding Pak Army solidarity march is fake
News_Text: Assistant Commissioner Karor Lal Esan issued a letter to Tehsildar Muhammad Iqbal and Naib Tehsildars Naeem Ud Din Muhammad Tahir and Baz Khan demanding an explanation for their failure to attend a rally organized to express solidarity with the Pakistan Army. The letter specified that in case of a lack of response disciplinary proceedings according to the Punjab Employees Efficiency Discipline Accountability (PEEDA) Act 2006 will begin.
Label: Fake

News_Title: The New York Times did not publish a front page story about Bajwa immigrating to the US after retiring
News_Text: a report about General Bajwa and his family moving to the US after his retirement was published on the front page of the New York Times. It seems the video was first published by digital news organisation Top Breaking News which could not be located through a Google search or on Twitter Facebook or Youtube due to its generic name. The post was captioned “As expected General Bajwa and his family returned to their country America!”
Label: Fake

News_Title: Punjab Food Authority did not seize frog meat in Lahore
News_Text: Social media post claim that five tons of frog meat was seized by the Punjab Food Authority (PFA) and Punjab Police and two people in Lahore were arrested in connection with the case. The meat is being used at hotels and restaurants in the city as a replacement for chicken.
Label: Fake

News_Title: This photo does not show former Pakistan Army chief in Pindi stadium
News_Text: A picture shows former Pakistan Army chief General (r) Qamar Javed Bajwa arriving at a stadium in Rawalpindi to watch a cricket match between Pakistan and England.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan is not closing down its consulate in Kandahar
News_Text: Pakistan is shutting down its consulate in Kandahar Afghanistan to protest against the Taliban government.The official Twitter account of the Consulate General of Pakistan Kandahar was hacked on 2 December 2022. The hacked account tweeted the false claim that the consulate would shut  down for two days to protest against the Taliban government.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Imran Khan did not say “Daily mail did not apologize wholeheartedly”
News_Text: Imran Khan said “I know Daily Mail did not genuinely apologize” with regards to the Daily Mail apology to Shahbaz Sharif. The false quote has been edited onto a Geo Headline template. Geo has neither published this statement nor has Imran Khan made such a statement.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Elon Musk did not tweet Imran Khan has the most fake followers on Twitter
News_Text: A screenshot circulating online shows a tweet from Elon Musk stating that Imran Khan has the largest number of fake followers on Twitter. The screenshot also shows a fake follower audit claiming that Imran Khan has 60.8% fake followers.
Label: Fake

News_Title: UAE has not banned visit visa for residents of certain Pakistani cities
News_Text: The UAE has banned visitors from certain cities across Pakistan from entering on a visit visa.UAE immigration authorities have rejected the claim and confirmed that they have not banned visitors from any city in Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Journalist Ahmad Noorani did not report that General Bajwa took a 50 crore bribe to oust Imran Khan
News_Text: Ahmad Noorani has reported that Asif Zardari and Nawaz Sharif gave General Bajwa a PKR 5 billion bribe to remove Imran Khan from power and disqualify him.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Clip of PTI supporter goes viral as football fan backpacking to FIFA World Cup in Qatar The elderly backpacker is actually a supporter of former prime minister Imran Khan’s Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) party and was jogging to join the Haqeeqi Azadi March from Lahore to Islamabad. The clip has no connection to the 2022 FIFA World Cup.
News_Text: A video shows a 70-year-old Pakistani man travelling by foot to attend the 2022 FIFA World Cup in Qatar.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Ishaq Dar did not suggest selling Pakistan’s nuclear assets
News_Text: A screenshot of journalist Shahzeb Khanzada’s tweet suggests that Finance Minister Ishaq Dar said that if the International Monetary Fund (IMF) does not help the country Pakistan may consider selling its nuclear assets. The finance minister did not make any such comment about selling Pakistan’s nuclear program. The screenshot doing the rounds on social media is doctored.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Imran Khan did not accept that leaked audio is real
News_Text: Journalist Iqrar ul Hasan claimed that Imran Khan in a recent interview did not deny that the recently leaked audio clips were legitimate implying he confessed they were real.  The interview clip shared by Hasan was taken out of context. PTI spokespersons have formally denied the audio’s veracity in multiple forums on behalf of Imran Khan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Misleading headlines about Google suspending paid apps in Pakistan
News_Text: Google has suspended the purchase of paid apps in Pakistan. The tech giant has suspended the purchase of carrier-paid apps in Pakistan via mobile credit only. But the payment to purchase paid apps can be made via credit or debit cards.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo being linked to Bannu CTD siege
News_Text: A photo shows soldiers being taken as hostages following a siege at the Counter-Terrorism Department’s (CTD) compound in Bannu Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP). The photo is old. It was featured in a March 2008 article.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan Railways to restore Green Line train in January 2023
News_Text: The Green Line train running between Karachi and Islamabad has been restored. The train line which was cancelled in August 2022 following heavy rains and floods will be restored from January 2023. The claim appears to be based on a fake notification doing the rounds on social media.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Imran Khan did not initiate the Mohmand Dam project in KP
News_Text: Former prime minister Imran Khan initiated the Mohmand Dam project.The idea behind the Mohmand Dam project was first initiated by the Water and Power Development Authority (WAPDA) in 1963. Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) conducted the project’s feasibility study in 2000. The project was further modified considering the 2008 crisis and the 2010 floods and then WAPDA entered into a mutual agreement with private companies from Australia Japan and within the country in 2017. While the PTI government did indeed revive the project it was initiated at least 50 years before Imran Khan formed the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP) government.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral notification allegedly released by the Cabinet Secretariat is fake
News_Text: A new financial emergency notification has been issued for the country on 20 December 2022 by the Cabinet Secretariat. The notification has been debunked by the Ministry of Information and Broadcasting fact-check Twitter handle.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Routine WhatsApp update shared misleadingly as breaking news
News_Text: A video claims that WhatsApp will not be operational for multiple users starting on 31 December 2022.The video is misleading as WhatsApp pulls support from different out-of-date operating systems every year. It is nothing new and is instead presented sensationally as a “breaking news” report that may confuse users.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video does not show dollars being smuggled out of Pakistan
News_Text: A video shows dollars being smuggled out of Pakistan into Afghanistan through the Chaman border.The video is from September 2021 when the Taliban claimed to have recovered US dollars and gold bars stashed away at the residence of Amrullah Saleh the ousted Afghan vice president.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistani preacher Maulana Tariq Jamil has not died
News_Text: Maulana Tariq Jamil has died.  Maulana Tariq Jamil has not died. There is no credible evidence or news report suggesting the same and his family have not made any public statements about this.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistani forces did not launch recent air strikes in Afghanistan
News_Text: Social media posts claim that Pakistani forces launched air strikes against the Tehreek-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) in the Nangarhar province of Afghanistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of doctors arguing in OT is from India not Pakistan
News_Text: A video shows surgeons arguing with nursing staff inside an operation theatre in Pakistan.The video depicts an incident from Umaid Hospital Jodphur Rajasthan in India in August 20177. It is not from Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: 50000 children were not born in Faisalabad in 10 days
News_Text: At least 50000 babies were born in Faisalabad in just ten days in December 2022 the most in any city in Pakistan.More than 50000 childbirths were registered in the Faisalabad division and over 25000 in the Faisalabad district between 10 and 20 December 2022 as part of a birth registration drive launched by the Punjab government. This included ‘late’ registrations as well.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo being linked to wheat crisis in Pakistan
News_Text: A photo shows people in long queues waiting to buy flour bags amid the looming wheat crisis in Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Power outage did not cause Pakistan to be wiped off nighttime world map
News_Text: A nighttime visual of the earth from space shows that Pakistan was wiped off the map and completely dark during a massive country-wide power outage.  The image is doctored. The map which is sourced from NASA Worldview is based on satellite imagery and did not show Pakistan being wiped off due to the power outage.
Label: Fake

News_Title: APTMA denies closure of textile mills across Pakistan
News_Text: All Pakistan Textile Mills Association (APTMA) has announced the closure of textile mills across the country from 31 December 2022. APTMA clarified that the news regarding the closure of the textile industry is baseless and fake.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo of jailed Afghan children is indeed from Karachi
News_Text: A viral photo of jailed Afghan children is not from any prison in Sindh.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Sniffer dog of Karachi police not stolen
News_Text: A sniffer dog of Karachi police has been stolen.No sniffer dog has been stolen. The SSU says they do not have police dogs and the K-9 Unit at the Garden Police Headquarters Karachi also refuted the claim.
Label: Fake

News_Title: PTI official tweets old video to slam Pakistan govt
News_Text: A video shows people in a scuffle over a bag of flour amid rising inflation.The video is in fact from September 2022 when a scuffle broke out among some flood victims over bags of ration provided by the government.
Label: Fake

News_Title: No the federal government has not increased passport fees
News_Text: The Directorate General of Immigration and Passports has issued a notification announcing an increase in the fees for passport issuance.The DGIP announced fees for the issuance of e-passports. The fees for machine-readable passports that are currently issued will remain the same.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo does not show Putin reading Imran Khan’s book
News_Text: A photo shows Russian President Vladimir Putin reading a book by Imran Khan titled ‘Pakistan: A Personal History’
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo of Hafiz Naeem and Malik Riaz passed off as recent
News_Text: A photo shows Jamaat-e-Islami’s Karachi chief Hafiz Naeem ur Rehman taking an oath of loyalty from property tycoon Malik Riaz.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of Instagrammer portrayed as Bilawal Bhutto dancing
News_Text:
A video shows Pakistan’s Foreign Minister Bilawal Bhutto Zardari dancing to a Bollywood song at an event.

Fact: Bilawal has been misidentified in the video. It features a media student Mehroz Baig who posted the video on his social media account on 12 January 2023
Label: Fake

News_Title: No this man is not Major General Faisal Naseer
News_Text: A social media picture claims that it is an image of Major General Faisal Naseer who serves as the Director General of Counter Intelligence at the Inter-Services Intelligence (ISI).The claim is false. The man in the image is Lt. General Sardar Hassan Azhar Hayat Corps Commander Peshawar; the image is falsely associated with General Naseer.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Maulana Tariq Jamil’s son not injured in car accident
News_Text: Maulana Yousaf Jamil the son of Pakistan’s famed television preacher Maulana Tariq Jamil has been critically injured in a traffic accident a photo circulating on social media shows.
Label: Fake

News_Title: This photo does not show Nawaz Sharif’s mother or grandmother
News_Text: A photo shows the mother and grandmother of former prime minister and Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) Supremo Nawaz Sharif and claims they played the drum in the streets of Amritsar in colonial India.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Siraj ul Haq did not claim to end corruption with PPP
News_Text: A news grab suggests that Jamaat-e-Islami’s (JI) chief Sirajul Haq said that his party will end corruption along with the Pakistan Peoples Party (PPP). The photo is from a 22 March 2022 meeting when Bilawal offered condolences to the JI chief over his mother’s death. The meeting was followed by a media talk during which Haq did not make any such statement.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo wrongly linked to January 2023 suicide blast in Peshawar
News_Text: A picture shows rescue authorities and others in the aftermath of a blast on 30 January 2023 in the Police Lines neighbourhood of Peshawar Pakistan. Yellow police tape is visible in the background of the scene of the bombing that left more than 30 dead.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Shahid Khaqan Abbasi did not quit Pakistan Muslim League (N)
News_Text: Neo News reported that PMLN leader Shahid Khaqan Abbasi has quit the party.The claim is false. Shahid Khaqan Abbasi remains a senior leader within the PMLN and a close ally of Imran Khan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Image shared as ‘faces of Sindh’ is actually from Punjab
News_Text: An image shows the state of people living in rural Sindh hinting at the impoverished state of the province.The image is in fact more than a decade old and shows affectees of the 2010 Pakistan flood in a village in Dera Ghazi Khan in the country’s Punjab province.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video linked with Peshawar blast in 2023
News_Text: A picture shows rescue authorities and others in the aftermath of a blast on 30 January 2023 in the Police Lines neighbourhood of Peshawar Pakistan. Yellow police tape is visible in the background of the scene of the bombing that left more than 30 dead.
Label: Fake

News_Title: No a barber did not cut off a customer’s ears over Imran Khan criticism
News_Text: A Geo News post which includes an image of dismembered ears among shorn hair claims that a barber cut off the ears of a man who criticised Imran Khan  No such incident took place and the news card is doctored. Soch Fact Check spoke to multiple Geo News employees who asserted that the organisation did not create or post such a visual on social media.
Label: Fake

News_Title: 2013 photo from Bangladesh passed off as struggling Pakistanis
News_Text: A post includes a photo of two seemingly impoverished Pakistani children having a meal and text stating that people in the country are worried due to inflation unemployment and poverty while those in power are focused on political battles.
Label: Fake

News_Title: LEAs carried out operations at Karachi Police HQ attack contrary to posts
News_Text: Following an attack on the Karachi police chief’s office on 17 February 2023 police left the building without putting up a fight against the terrorists and the Pakistan Army refused to carry out an operation.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Karachi police HQ attack: Twitter account shares false info on KPO incident
News_Text: A Twitter account claims that Section 144 has been imposed in Karachi and authorities have advised people to stay at home after more than 10 Baloch freedom fighters attacked the Karachi police chief’s office at Shahrah-e-Faisal alongside an image of the site of the attack.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Shireen Mazari shares doctored Al Jazeera screengrab
News_Text: Shireen Mazari says the government of Pakistan has bowed to their US counterparts by allowing the Americans to use the country’s airspace for military purposes despite the proposal being rejected by the cabinet.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan Super League 2023 has not been postponed
News_Text: The eighth edition of the Pakistan Super League (PSL) has been postponed following an attack on the Karachi police chief’s office on 17 February 2023. The Asia Cup cricket tournament is moving out of Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Newspaper publishes false info about murdered Peshawar lecturer
News_Text: A lecturer at the Islamia College University (ICU) in Peshawar who was shot dead on 19 February 2023 was involved in drug peddling.The lecturer Dr Bashir Ahmad was acquitted of all charges in a case of drug peddling that was brought against him in 2017. He was formally cleared in 2019 according to a court order
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video of slaughterhouse raid wrongly linked to inflation
News_Text: A video shows Pakistanis slaughtering dogs and donkeys for meat amid the economic crisis and skyrocketing inflation.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Maryam Nawaz did not say PTI supporters are jealous of her beauty
News_Text: A news grab of Hum News’ bulletin suggests that Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz leader Maryam Nawaz has said that people from the Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf are jealous of her beauty.
Label: Fake

News_Title: K-Electric has not increased electricity prices during peak hours
News_Text: A visual with the K-Electric’s logo states that the per-unit electricity charges effective “today” are PKR 42 during peak hours (6:00-10:30 PM) and PKR 24 during off-peak hours (the remaining time of the day). It is unclear which day or date the word “today” in the message refers to. Further the text advises people to “use electricity accordingly” and to “switch off non-essential electricity” during peak hours lest they get a hefty bill.
Label: Fake

News_Title: 2009 video of ATM mugging in Karachi viral on social media
News_Text: CCTV footage shows a recent mugging at an ATM in Karachi. The CCTV footage is old and can be found online as early as April 2009. The video does not show a recent mugging at an ATM in Karachi.
Label: Fake

News_Title: WHO did not publish a list of “seven biggest brain damaging habits”
News_Text: WHO guidelines on brain stroke claim 7 “biggest brain damaging habits”
Label: Fake

News_Title: Shaukat Tarin was not arrested by the Federal Investigation Agency
News_Text: A viral social media post claims that PTI leader Shaukat Tarin had been arrested by the FIA.He has not been arrested but he has been charged and may be taken into custody in the near future.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Zartaj Gul shares doctored image of Imran Khan sitting next to “poor” woman
News_Text: Zartaj Gul tweeted a photo of Imran Khan sitting next to a woman with the caption “he was a strange king; he used to seat the poor in the front at a gathering of kings.”
Label: Fake

News_Title: Megavac is not a new medical invention
News_Text: A group of Indian doctors have invented a piece of advanced equipment to remove coronary artery blockages called Megavac a mechanical thrombectomy system which removes blockages mitigating the need for open-heart surgery.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo from Afghanistan shared as people fleeing Pakistan
News_Text: A photo shows a huge crowd in Islamabad with some people holding passports and fleeing Pakistan due to the current economic crisis.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pink Bus is the first-ever women-only service in Sindh not Pakistan
News_Text: The government of Sindh on Thursday announced to launch pink buses – the first bus service in Pakistan that will be exclusively for women. The service is expected to start next month.
Label: Fake

News_Title: KP’s forensic laboratory is in operations since 2018
News_Text: Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf failed to build a forensic laboratory for DNA testing in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP).The Forensic Science Lab in KP became functional on 6 February 2018 although the lab was established three years before then to conduct DNA profiling.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Simulation portrayed as Indian plane’s emergency landing at a Pakistan airport
News_Text: A video shows an Indian aeroplane making an emergency landing at an airport in Pakistan.a video showing an aeroplane marked ‘Air Austriana’ landing at an airport but with one of its landing gears stuck faltering and zigzagging midair before bouncing on the runway hitting its engines on the ground and skidding to a halt.
Label: Fake

News_Title: ‘Fact-check’ denying Dutch researcher predicted earthquake in Pakistan is false
News_Text: the prediction of an earthquake in Pakistan India or Afghanistan were “falsely attributed” to Dutch researcher Frank Hoogerbeets. It further states that none of the three aforementioned countries’ names or those of any other South Asian nation
Label: Fake

News_Title: Image of model wearing leg plaster cast is doctored
News_Text: A photo of a model walking on a ramp with a plaster cast on her leg during a fashion show in Pakistan. The model’s look is apparently inspired by the cast Imran Khan wore on his leg following a gun attack in 2022.
Label: Fake

News_Title: COMSATS lecturer was terminated over ‘controversial’ question not suspended
News_Text: A visiting faculty member who included the Julie and Mark vignette as a question in a quiz paper for his students at the COMSATS University Islamabad was suspended following a moral uproar in Pakistan according to the
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video of cakes ‘spiked’ with pills to ‘sterilise’ Muslim kids viral
News_Text: A video shows pills found inside cakes by Turkish brand Luppo to subtly “sterilise” Muslim children in Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: No a naked girl did not attack media at Aurat March 2023
News_Text: The caption of a video posted on Facebook claims that a naked girl attacked the media at the 2023 Aurat March in Lahore Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Imran Khan did not say ‘hope lies with the establishment’
News_Text: A Dawn report quotes Imran Khan as saying “hope lies with the establishment in ending this farce” in a live address on 15 March 2022.After a day-long escalation continued between PTI supporters and law enforcement agencies outside ex-premier Imran Khan’s residence the Lahore High Court (LHC) on Wednesday stopped the police operation at Zaman Park till 10am tomorrow (March 16) while the Islamabad High Court (IHC) disposed of a plea seeking the cancellation of the PTI chief’s arrest warrants.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video from Karachi portrayed as Zaman Park protest in Lahore
News_Text: A video shows a large number of people gathered at Zaman Park in Lahore to stop Imran Khan from being arrested.The clip is old and does not show Zaman Park. It is from a protest against Khan’s ouster back in April 2022 when his supporters gathered near Millennium Mall in Karachi.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Facebook page live streams old speech of Imran Khan as new
News_Text: Imran Khan addressed his party workers and supporters in Zaman Park Lahore on 14 March 2023 and his speech was broadcastThe live stream in question actually shows an old speech from May 2022 and was not filmed at his residence. However Khan has been speaking to the media and his supporters from his Zaman Park residence.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video of petrol pump ablaze is from Narowal not Lahore
News_Text: A video shows a petrol pump in Lahore being set on fire to protest against fuel hikes in Pakistan.The video is from June 2020 when a petrol station in Narowal Punjab was set on fire by people protesting against the petrol cartel.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo does not show injured police officers in Zaman Park clashes
News_Text: Clashes broke out between the police and PTI supporters on 14 March 2023 ahead of PTI chief Imran Khan’s possible arrest outside his residence in
Label: Fake

News_Title: No this image does not show surveillance helicopters over Zaman Park
News_Text: A picture shows a helicopter surveilling Lahore’s Zaman Park where PTI workers and supporters had gathered for a rally in the wee hours of 9 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo from Afghanistan wrongly linked to Zaman Park clashes
News_Text: A photo shows a police officer hitting a woman with a gun’s butt at Zaman Park Lahore. The photo is old. It actually shows a Taliban security personnel threatening a woman in Kabul Afghanistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old images wrongly linked to 2023 earthquake in Pakistan
News_Text: Different images on social media show damaged houses that collapsed after a sizable earthquake hit a number of countries including Pakistan on 21 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photos of ‘mysterious red glow’ wrongly linked to Pakistan earthquake
News_Text: A group of photos taken in March 2023 show a “mysterious red glow” over the Atlantic shortly after a powerful earthquake hit Pakistan Afghanistan and India.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Turkey’s 2020 image falsely linked to recent earthquake in Pakistan
News_Text: An image on social media shows rescue workers standing in front of a collapsed building after a sizable earthquake hit several countries including Pakistan on 21 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo does not show police officer killed in Zaman Park clashes
News_Text: A photo shows a police officer killed when Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) workers fired bullets during the recant stand-off at Zaman Park in Lahore.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo of tear gas shells is from 2020 not Zaman Park
News_Text: A photo shows a pile of tear gas shells used by police against Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf’s supporters during the recent Zaman Park clashes in March 2022.Clashes broke out between the police and Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) supporters on 14 March 2023 ahead of PTI chief Imran Khan’s possible arrest outside his residence in
Label: Fake

News_Title: TTP did not issue a statement to support PTI in elections
News_Text: A Tehreek-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) press release says all political parties should vote for PTI in upcoming elections in Punjab and KP.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Image of PTI worker holding gun is photoshopped and not from 2023
News_Text: A Twitter image shows a Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) worker hanging out the window of a van with a weapon in his hand during the recent rally on 8 March in Lahore.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video from Gujranwala shared as PTI’s election rally in Lahore
News_Text: A video shows a large public rally in Lahore during Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf’s (PTI) election campaign for the Punjab elections in March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Image of policeman with head injuries is from 2021
News_Text: An image shows a police officer wearing an ASI badge with severe head injuries after the recent skirmishes at Zaman Park where PTI supporters attacked the police.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Miftah Ismail did not say that military helped remove Khan from power
News_Text: Miftah Ismail said that Imran Khan is a good politician the military helped remove him from power and elections should be held within 90 days.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Tiktok video shared old clip from Hamid Mir’s show claiming it shows Imran Khan’s recent Minar-e-Pakistan jalsa
News_Text: A video posted by Tiktok user @badshahkhan123pti shows a beeper from journalist Hamid Mir’s show that says “Imran Khan’s historic jalsa at minar-e-pakistan lahore” and claims that it is from Imran Khan’s recent March 2023 rally.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video does not show PTI women and trans people attacking police
News_Text: A video shows PTI supporters — transgender people and women — attacking the police during the recent clashes in Zaman Park Lahore.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo passed off as PTI’s recent Minar-e-Pakistan rally
News_Text: A photo shows Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf’s rally at Minar-e-Pakistan Lahore held on 25 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old video from Turkey linked to recent earthquake in Pakistan
News_Text: A video shows several buildings collapsing after a sizable earthquake hit many countries including Pakistan on 21 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Satirical article about Charles III offering kingship to Imran Khan passed off as real news
News_Text:
King Charles III offered Imran Khan to become the King of the United Kingdom. Imran Khan the former prime minister and chief of the Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) alongside King Charles III of the UK as well as the following text:

“KING CHARLES III OFFERED IMRAN KHAN TO BECOME KING OF UK KHAN REJECTED”
Label: Fake

News_Title: Quote by Israel’s Benjamin Netanyahu about Pakistan misrepresented
News_Text: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu was asked in an interview “What is the biggest problem facing the next generation and what should we do to solve it today?”. He responded by saying the main goal is to stop militant Islamic regimes from getting nuclear weapons and that Pakistan is one of the two countries which are a threat to Israel.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Lahore Police have not arrested a child for begging
News_Text: Lahore Police have arrested a minor boy for “dressing up as a girl and begging”.The child has not been arrested but handed over to the Child Protection & Welfare Bureau (CP&WB).
Label: Fake

News_Title: Photo showing Swat road damaged due to earthquake is not from 2023
News_Text: A photo shows a giant crack in a road in Swat’s Shangla region after a 6.5-magnitude earthquake hit northwestern areas of Pakistan on 21 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video from Aurat March Islamabad misrepresented as PTI protest in Lahore
News_Text: A video shows a group of police officers in Lahore in a verbal altercation with women belonging to the PTI with one of the cops yelling “Don’t touch me” and another pushing a woman. The clip goes on to show police baton-charging people near a container and behind barbed wire at the scene.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Fawad Chaudhry shares old picture as Zaman Park gathering
News_Text: An image featuring a large group of people law enforcement officers and multiple barricades is from Zaman Park Lahore where supporters of Imran Khan have gathered to prevent authorities from arresting him.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Claim Peshawar university lecturer was killed over blasphemy is false
News_Text: Peshawar’s Islamia College University lecturer Dr Bashir Ahmad was killed over a blasphemy allegation.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Does this viral video show CJP Umar Ata Bandial’s daughter dancing?
News_Text: A video shows Sahar Bandial the daughter of Chief Justice Umar Ata Bandial dancing with a group of young women.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Tunnel claimed to be Sardar Khetran’s private jail is actually in England
News_Text: A video shows the private jail of Sardar Abdul Rehman Khetran where the Barkhan murder victims were kept.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Imran Riaz Khan shares false misleading photos from PTI clash in Lahore
News_Text: A visual shows pictures of three different PTI workers allegedly injured during clashes with the police in Lahore on 8 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Picture claiming to show Imran Khan ‘escaping’ is actually of Hamza Shahbaz
News_Text: A picture shows Imran Khan “escaping” arrest at his Zaman Park residence in Lahore by climbing out through a ladder.
Label: Fake

News_Title: This video does not show a protest against Pakistan Army
News_Text: A video shows supporters of Imran Khan protesting against the Pakistan Army.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old videos of airport brawls portrayed as new incidents in Karachi
News_Text: Two videos show Airport Security Force (ASF) officials misbehaving and manhandling passengers at Karachi’s Jinnah International Airport.
Label: Fake

News_Title: No the herb fagonia cannot cure cancer
News_Text: “I have seen 50% of last-stage cancer disappear with the use of fagonia herb in two months” wrote a Twitter user on May 24 “It is a green powder that has been crushed after cutting and cleaning fresh herbs.”
Label: Fake

News_Title: Doctor who prepared Zille Shah’s postmortem has not been transferred
News_Text: Online posts viewed thousands of times on Twitter and Facebook are falsely claiming that a doctor who prepared the postmortem report of Zille Shah a Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) supporter has been suspended as he did not bow to official pressure when drafting the report which showed unexplainable injuries on Shah’s body.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Contrary to claims no Afghan national has been arrested by police outside Imran Khan’s house
News_Text: On March 14 and 15 after the police clashed with supporters of the Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) in Lahore near the residence of PTI’s chairman Imran Khan multiple social media accounts alleged that the majority of the men arrested by the cops were Afghan nationals who had been brought to guard Khan’s home.
Label: Fake

News_Title: What are the salaries benefits of the Supreme Court judges?
News_Text: Multiple social media accounts allege that a judge of the top court of Pakistan earns over Rs1.7 million per month including benefits.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Yes it’s mandatory for students in Gujranwala to learn about the Pakistan Army
News_Text: A notification has circulated online alongside the claim that schools in Gujranwala Punjab have been directed to ensure students are taught about the achievements of the Pakistan military every day.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Is the video of the petrol bomb old?
News_Text: A video circulating on Pakistani social media purportedly shows a Molotov cocktail being tossed from inside former prime minister Imran Khan’s residence in Lahore at a police armoured vehicle on March 15.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Posts falsely claim Justice Mandokhail is related to PML-N politician
News_Text: Shortly after a Supreme Court judge Justice Jamal Khan Mandokhail recused himself from a top court bench hearing a petition by the Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) into the delay in the election for the Punjab Assembly social media users began circulating a claim that the judge was the brother of a politician from the ruling Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N).
Label: Fake

News_Title: Was Asif Ali Zardari featured in a Netherlands school book?
News_Text: A photo being shared online purportedly shows a chapter from a textbook in the Netherlands on the alleged corruption of Pakistan’s former president Asif Ali Zardari.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Posts falsely claim Nawaz Sharif threatened to destroy the country
News_Text: The Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) has claimed that former prime minister Nawaz Sharif has threatened to “destroy the country” if the Supreme Court’s decision in the Punjab assembly election case did not favor his political party the ruling-Pakistan Muslim League-N (PML-N).
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan govt is not banning PKR 5,000 banknote
News_Text: PKR 5,000 banknotes are being discontinued across Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: SAMAA TV runs misinformation on insurance cover provided by SBP
News_Text: The SBP has warned people that funds upwards of PKR 500,000 kept in bank accounts are not safe anymore.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Notification of ban on PKR, 5000 note is false
News_Text: A notification by the Ministry of Finance claims that the 5000 rupees note will be banned in Pakistan from 30 September 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Hadiqa Kiyani built two mosques, not two hundred
News_Text: Pakistani celebrity Hadiqa Kiyani built 370 homes, two maternity centers and 200 mosques for  survivors in the aftermath of the 2022 monsoon floods in Balochistan, Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of father and daughter laughing is not from Gaza
News_Text: A video claims to show a father and daughter laughing together to cope with the recent bombing in Gaza.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of ‘Big Ben’ painted in white is not from 2023
News_Text: A video shows that London’s Elizabeth Tower, also known as the ‘Big Ben’, was painted white by “Jihadis” (a term used for Muslim fighters) in 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Taylor Swift did not postpone Eras tour film screenings in Israel
News_Text: Taylor Swift’s Eras tour film was cancelled in Israel over the Gaza conflict.
Label: Fake

News_Title: CII did not declare first wife’s permission unnecessary for second marriage
News_Text: The Council of Islamic Ideology (CII) has declared it unneccessary for a husband to get permission from his first wife before remarrying.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Is Disney producing a film based on a famed pornographic video?
News_Text: Disney is producing a new film called “Two Girls ONE CUP”, the poster of which has already been released.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old pictures linked to dubious claim dog meat was seized from KP restaurants
News_Text: KP Police carried out a raid at local restaurants that were found preparing meals with dog meat; accompanying pictures show various dishes, as well as carcasses, recovered during the operation.
Label: Fake

News_Title: State Bank of Pakistan has not introduced a PKR 300 banknote
News_Text: The caretaker government has issued a Rs 300 banknote for the people of Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: This is not an authentic photo of Imran Khan with his mother
News_Text: A photograph shows Imran Khan sitting at the feet of his mother, Shaukat Khanum.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Maggi and other instant noodles are not made from rotten flour and pig marrow
News_Text: A viral video on WhatsApp claims that Maggi instant noodles are manufactured from flour that has rotted for four to five days as well as pig marrow.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Twitter users share old photos of the Wazir mansion claiming that it is in a dilapidated state
News_Text: Wazir Mansion in Karachi, where Quaid e Azam was born, is in a dilapidated state with stagnant sewage water on the street right in front of the Wazir Mansion.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral video does not show Virat Kohli and Babar Azam hanging out
News_Text: A video shows former Indian captain Virat Kohli and current Pakistani captain Babar Azam enjoying themselves together in Faisalabad during the IND-U19 visit to Pakistan in 2006.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Behind-the-scenes video of Mahira Khan shared in misleading context
News_Text: A social media user shares a video clip of Mahira Khan and states a longer video contains sensitive content.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video clips of Punjab police torturing women are not from recent PTI arrests
News_Text: Social media videos claim to show the police torturing  Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) supporters who were involved in the 9 May 2023 clashes.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old doctored photo of Fazlur Rehman with Jack Daniel’s resurfaces
News_Text: A picture shows Fazlur Rehman sitting in an aeroplane with a bottle of whiskey and a half-filled glass on the armrest beside him.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Toyota Indus Motors is not leaving Pakistan, says company
News_Text: Toyota Indus Motors is set to permanently shut down manufacturing in Pakistan and leave Pakistan permanently.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Bayer Pharmaceuticals has not announced closure of business in Pakistan
News_Text: Bayer Pharmaceuticals has announced they will halt operations in Pakistan, and company assets have been sold to another business. The news was shared by X (formerly Twitter) user (@asadnasir2000) and he cited a Daily Times article titled, “Bayer pharmaceutical company announces closing business in Pakistan,” as a source.
Label: Fake

News_Title: The oldest olive tree is in Greece, not Israel
News_Text: The world’s oldest olive tree is found in “Jerusalem, Israel” and is “estimated to be over 3000 years old”; a picture accompanying the claim shows a gnarly old tree with an extremely thick trunk.
Label: Fake

News_Title: The construction of Shaukat Khanum Karachi has not been halted
News_Text: All construction work has been halted at the Shaukat Khanum Karachi building, and its intended inauguration for 14 August 2023 has now been postponed.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan has not banned women from going overseas on labour visas
News_Text: Pakistan has banned women from going overseas on labour visas, preventing women from working in nursing, teaching, and hospitality through legal work permits.
Label: Fake

News_Title: People from Hunza are not cancer-free due to apricot seeds
News_Text: A viral video posted on Instagram and Facebook claims the people from Hunza never get cancer, the average age among them used to be 160, apricot seeds can prevent cancer,, and that their broken bones heal in days, and they don’t get wrinkles.
Label: Fake

News_Title: This video does not show a dirty British Airways flight from Pakistan to London
News_Text: A video shows a littered aisle, as well as a dirty toilet, including tissues, water, and human excrement at the edge of the chair commode, inside a British Airways flight from Pakistan to London.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Claims that minor domestic worker died after torture are false
News_Text: A minor domestic worker who was allegedly tortured by a judge’s wife in Islamabad has died of her injuries.
Label: Fake

News_Title: News claiming Mari Matta Mandir in Soldier Bazaar was not demolished are false
News_Text: Mari Matta Mandir in Soldier Bazaar was not demolished; instead, a woman’s private property adjacent to the temple was destroyed with her consent.
Label: Fake

News_Title: News claiming 72% of women smoke in Pakistan is false
News_Text: Social media posts claim that the percentage of women who smoke in Pakistan has surged to 72%, citing the Pakistan Tobacco Board (PTB) as the source.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video from ABP news showing impact of Cyclone Biparjoy is misleading
News_Text: A video from ABP News shows terrifying visuals of torrential rainfall and extreme winds in Karachi ahead of cyclone Biparjoy.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral image claiming to show a child marriage is wrong
News_Text: Viral image shows a 9-year-old Hindu girl Reshma who was forcibly abducted, taken to a Sufi shrine, converted to Islam and married to a 45-year-old Muslim man from Jacobabad named Wazir Hussain
Label: Fake

News_Title: Hrithik Roshan did not voice support for Imran Khan
News_Text: Bollywood actor Hrithik Roshan has requested his fans to support former prime minister Imran Khan.

News_Title: Aima Baig did not say she had a crush on her brother
News_Text: Singer Aima Baig has said that she has a crush on her brother, who is seven years older than her.

News_Title: Government did not announce a public holiday for Pakistan Martyrs Day
News_Text: A notification claims that the federal government has announced a public holiday on the occasion of Youm-e-Takreem Shuhada-e-Pakistan or Pakistan Martyrs Day.

News_Title: Video of goats thrown out of moving truck is not from Pakistan
News_Text: A viral video shows a man dumping goats from a moving truck on Karachi’s Super Highway.

News_Title: No, mountains of gold did not emerge as the Euphrates dried up
News_Text: A mountain of gold has been found in the Euphrates River.
Label: Fake

News_Text: Geo News reported that New Zealand cricketer Siimon Doull sayd he was living in Pakistan like a prisoner; he was not allowed to go out and was not given any food for many days. The cricketer said he has suffered mental torture and is glad he has now escaped Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Digital art passed off as real scud clouds over Sydney
News_Text: A picture shows “skud clouds” over Sydney, Australia.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Images do not show an Algerian mosque revealed after a sandstorm
News_Text: A mosque appeared in an Algerian desert after a sandstorm.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistani actress Saeeda Imtiaz has not died
News_Text: Pakistani-American actress and model Saeeda Imtiaz died.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video showing apparent shipwreck is not from Libya
Label: Fake

News_Title: Lahore Police have not arrested a child for begging
News_Text: Lahore Police have arrested a minor boy for “dressing up as a girl and begging”.

News_Title: No, this picture is not from PTI’s 2023 Minar-e-Pakistan Jalsa
News_Text: An image shared on social media shows a Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) public gathering at Lahore’s Minar-e-Pakistan on 25 March 2023
Label: Fake

News_Title: Salman Ahmed of Junoon was not arrested recently
News_Text: Salman Ahmad of Junoon has been arrested recently.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Turkey’s 2020 image falsely linked to recent earthquake in Pakistan
News_Text: An image on social media shows rescue workers standing in front of a collapsed building after a sizable earthquake hit several countries, including Pakistan, on 21 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old images wrongly linked to 2023 earthquake in Pakistan
News_Text: Different images on social media show damaged houses that collapsed after a sizable earthquake hit a number of countries, including Pakistan, on 21 March 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: No, a naked girl did not attack media at Aurat March 2023
News_Text: The caption of a video posted on Facebook claims that a naked girl attacked the media at the 2023 Aurat March in Lahore, Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of a cat being rescued is not from Turkey 2023 earthquake
News_Text: A social media video apparently shows a cat being rescued after a powerful earthquake hit Turkey and Syria earlier this month.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Clips of Turkish actor are from an old drama, not earthquake site
News_Text: A social media video claims that it shows Turkish actor Burak Ozcivit helping victims in the aftermath of the recent earthquake in Turkey.
Label: Fake

News_Title: False anti-Islam quote attributed to Salman Rushdie
News_Text: Author Salman Rushdie recently said, “The large majority of peaceful Muslims don’t matter because I was attacked by just one Muslim who followed Quran. All religions are not same because they have not codified death to whoever doesn’t believe in their religion. On my life I want to warn the world that Islam will not rest till every other society, culture, and religion is either annihilated or converted.”
Label: Fake

News_Title: No, a barber did not cut off a customer’s ears over Imran Khan criticism
News_Text: A Geo News post, which includes an image of dismembered ears among shorn hair, claims that a barber cut off the ears of a man who criticised Imran Khan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video does not show Baloch students protesting for freedom from Pakistan
News_Text: A social media video shows Baloch students chanting and demanding freedom from Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: This photo does not show Nawaz Sharif’s mother or grandmother
News_Text: A photo shows the mother and grandmother of former prime minister and Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) Supremo, Nawaz Sharif, and claims they played the drum in the streets of Amritsar in colonial India.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Fake pictures of snow in Islamabad got viral
News_Text: Pictures in various posts claim to show recent snowfall in Islamabad.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Iran has not abolished morality police
News_Text: The Islamic Republic of Iran has abolished the Guidance Patrol — commonly referred to as the  “morality police” — in response to months of protests that erupted after the death of Mahsa Amini, a 22-year-old girl, allegedly in custody.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Brazil has not permitted citizens to kill bike-riding muggers
News_Text: The Government of Brazil has permitted its citizens to start killing bike-riding muggers in a bid to bring down street crime.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Half of Pakistanis did not say they would leave the country if they get the chance
News_Text: According to a survey conducted by the Pakistan Institute of Development Economics (PIDE), half of all Pakistanis will leave Pakistan if they have a chance
Label: Fake

News_Title: Rat munching on cake in a meeting is not from Balochistan CS Office
News_Text: A social media video shows a rat munching on a piece of cake during a meeting at the Chief Secretary’s Office in Balochistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Punjab Food Authority did not seize frog meat in Lahore
News_Text: Social media post claim that five tons of frog meat was seized by the Punjab Food Authority (PFA) and Punjab Police, and two people in Lahore were arrested in connection with the case. The meat is being used at hotels and restaurants in the city as a replacement for chicken.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Canada is not issuing visas through lottery
News_Text: Viral social media messages claim that applications for Canada’s visa lottery program are open. It says that the Canadian Government has increased the number of visas issued to people through visa lottery by 500% in 2022. The viral message is accompanied by a link to sign up for the visa lottery.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan did not win the World Cup of Polo Championship 2022
News_Text: Pakistan won the World Polo Championship 2022 by beating Mexico in the Final 11-8.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Sindh Government’s People’s Bus was not trapped in a sinkhole in Larkana
News_Text: An image on social media claims to show the People’s Bus stuck in a sinkhole in Larkana.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral message warning of crimes using drug-laced visiting cards is false
News_Text: According to a viral WhatsApp message, people in Lahore’s Defence Housing Authority (DHA) have been handing out visiting cards laced with a debilitating drug called burundanga to unsuspecting motorists stopped at petrol stations in order to rob, kidnap or sexually assault them.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Joyland does not show extramarital affair between woman and her husband’s brother
News_Text: Joyland depicts a sexual relationship between a woman and her husband’s brother, which results in the character getting pregnant
Label: Fake

News_Title: Scientists did not create 3D models of Abrahamic prophets
News_Text: Multiple images are being shared on social media, claiming that scientists at universities have created models of what Adam and other Abrahamic prophets looked like. The models resemble contemporary celebrities.
Label: Fake

News_Title: British-Pakistani did not fly to Pakistan to vote for PTI in by-elections
News_Text: Diaspora Pakistani Sarim Rashid flew out to Pakistan from the UK to cast a vote for PTI in the October 2022 by-elections. He flew in just in time for the elections and flew out three hours later back to the UK.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old image of Kabul suicide attack victim shared with false context
News_Text: An image of a woman with facial scars is being shared on social media with captions that claim she survived a recent suicide attack at a tuition center in Kabul, Afghanistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video showing Kidney Hill ‘witch’ is actually VFX artist Joseph Njovu’s work
News_Text: A “witch” was filmed hovering in Kidney Hill Park in Karachi, Pakistan and strange noises heard by park officials in the dead of night. The person who shot the video was down with a 104°F fever.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Mahenoor Soomro denies marriage rumours with Bilawal Bhutto
News_Text: Foreign Minister Bilawal Bhutto-Zardari is tying the knot with Mahenoor Soomro, granddaughter of Pakistan Peoples Party’s founding member late Ruqiya Khanum Soomro.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old image shared as pro-hijab protest in Iran 2022
News_Text: An image widely shared on social media claims that it shows pro-government rallies in Iran held to counter anti-hijab protests in September 2022.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of father dancing at daughter’s funeral is not from Iran
News_Text: A video shared on social media claims that it shows a man at the funeral of his daughter, who was purportedly killed by Iranian morality police for not covering her hair.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Politician misrepresents NADRA data as people who changed their gender
News_Text: A data table shows that 28,723 people changed the gender they were assigned at birth through the National Database and Registration Authority (NADRA) from July 2018 to June 2021.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of firing incident from Pakistan, not Afghanistan
News_Text: A video shows gunmen opening fire at a crowd in the Pul-e-Khumri area of Afghanistan, reportedly killing 51 people over a dispute about a donkey.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Mohenjo-Daro will not be removed from the UNESCO list of World Heritage sites
News_Text: Mohenjo-Daro will likely be removed from the list of World Heritage sites.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Extravagant birthday from Sialkot wrongly attributed to Bakhtawar Bhutto
News_Text: A video of a grand birthday party that had gone viral on social media is from Bakhtawar Bhutto Zardari’s son’s birthday.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Fire in China skyscraper did not kill 600 people
News_Text: The tallest skyscraper in China -fourth tallest building in the world- caught fire, leaving six hundred people dead. It was the biggest fire since 9/11. An additional claim in social media posts argues that the fire was an American conspiracy plan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral tweet of Afghan player apologising for feud with Asif Ali is doctored
News_Text: A screenshot of Afghan cricket player Farid Malik apologising after for a recent on-field feud with Pakistan’s Asif Ali was widely shared on social media
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video does not show giant waves destroying Emaar apartments in Karachi
News_Text: A video of an apartment building being destroyed by giant waves was taken at Emaar Apartments in Defence Housing Authority (DHA) Phase 8 in Karachi, Pakistan
Label: Fake

News_Title: Video of buried baby being rescued is not from recent floods in Pakistan
News_Text: A viral video on social media shows a small child being rescued in the aftermath of recent floods in Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral video of leopard attacking cow is not from Pakistan
News_Text: A viral video of a leopard attacking a cow on the roadside is being shared with claims that the incident happened near Margalla Hills, Islamabad
Label: Fake

News_Title: Cloudburst time-lapse is from Perth, Australia, not Jamshoro
News_Text: A cloudburst time lapse is being shared on social media with the claim that it is from Jamshoro during the torrential monsoon of 2022.
Label: Fake

News_Title: No, Johnny Depp did not participate in Ashura procession in Karbala
News_Text: Actor Johnny Depp participated in an Ashura ritual in Karbala, Iraq on 10 Muharram of Islamic calendar.
Label: Fake

News_Title: World Animal Protection did not condemn arrest of Shahbaz Gill
News_Text: The World Animal Protection (WAP) condemned the arrest of former Pakistani prime minister Imran Khan’s aide, Dr Shahbaz Gill, in a Twitter post.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Main accused in Faisalabad kidnapping, torture case has not been released on bail
News_Text: ARY News reported that businessman Sheikh Danish, the main accused in a recent case of kidnapping and torture in Faisalabad, has been released on bail.

News_Title: Anchor wrongly links Brazil’s mid-surgery assault case to Quetta harassment incident
News_Text: News anchor Syed Ali Haider talks about a case of sexual harassment at Quetta’s Heart and General Hospital. He links a viral clip of a doctor sexually assaulting a patient during a surgery to a video of a woman demanding justice for being harassed during surgery.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral image claiming to be from the official national Independence Day celebration is old
News_Text: An image of a female dancer in front of a portrait of Quaid e Azam is from the official national day celebrations held at the Jinnah Convention Center, Islamabad
Label: Fake

News_Title: Facebook video wrongly claims married couple are siblings
News_Text: The title of a Facebook video claims that two biological siblings in Pakistan married each other.
Label: Fake

News_Title: The video of the Azaan on an Indian talent show is doctored
News_Text: A video has been circulating on Facebook that is captioned “A beautiful rendition of the Azaan in India’s biggest talent show”.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Bank Alfalah is not blocking donations for Palestine
News_Text: The Pakistani government has asked all banks to stop accepting donations for Palestine. A leaked internal memo from Bank Alfalah is being used to claim that the bank does not accept donations for the account of the Palestinian government.
Label: Fake

News_Title: False reports emerge about death of India’s Amartya Sen
News_Text: Amartya Sen has died.
Label: Fake

News_Title: SAMAA TV runs misinformation on insurance cover provided by SBP
News_Text: The SBP has warned people that funds upwards of PKR 500,000 kept in bank accounts are not safe anymore.
Label: Fake

News_Title: State Bank of Pakistan has not introduced a PKR 300 banknote
News_Text: The caretaker government has issued a Rs 300 banknote for the people of Pakistan.
Label: Fake

News_Title: False image shows fake currency notes with specific serial numbers
News_Text: A viral WhatsApp message claims that Pakistani currency notes in denominations of 500, 1000, or 5000 rupees bearing serial numbers beginning with AF, CE, or HO are counterfeit. It further suggests that the State Bank of Pakistan (SBP) has released a press statement to alert the public.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Notification of ban on PKR, 5000 note is false
News_Text: A notification by the Ministry of Finance claims that the 5000 rupees note will be banned in Pakistan from 30 September 2023.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Capital TV runs old video as IMF response to Pakistan electricity protests
News_Text: Capital TV ran news that the IMF has issued a “Big Statement” over the protests against the higher electricity bills across Pakistan, demanding the rich be taxed and poor be provided subsidies.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Anchor exaggerates petrol prices in Canada compared to Pakistan
News_Text: Anchor Fiza Riaz says a litre of petrol costs 173.9 Canadian dollars in Canada.

News_Title: Viral post about imminent billion-dollar-plus defence sale to Middle East is misleading
News_Text: Pakistan is in the final stages of signing a billion-dollar-plus defence sale to a Middle Eastern country.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Toyota Indus Motors is not leaving Pakistan, says company
News_Text: Toyota Indus Motors is set to permanently shut down manufacturing in Pakistan and leave Pakistan permanently.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Bayer Pharmaceuticals has not announced closure of business in Pakistan
News_Text: Bayer Pharmaceuticals has announced they will halt operations in Pakistan, and company assets have been sold to another business. The news was shared by X (formerly Twitter) user (@asadnasir2000) and he cited a Daily Times article titled, “Bayer pharmaceutical company announces closing business in Pakistan,” as a source.
Label: Fake

News_Title: WhatsApp forward falsely claims government has passed bill to reduce pensions
News_Text: A viral Whatsapp forward message claims that the government has passed a bill which will result in government employees receiving pensions according to their basic salary when they were recruited, instead of their last salary slip.

News_Title: Ishaq Dar was back in the country on 25 January

News_Title: No, mountains of gold did not emerge as the Euphrates dried up

Label: Fake

News_Title: Images do not show an Algerian mosque revealed after a sandstorm

News_Title: Video does not show Baloch students protesting for freedom from Pakistan

News_Title: Rubber used to make chicken nuggets? Viral video based on false narrative

News_Title: Maggi and other instant noodles are not made from rotten flour and pig marrow
News_Text: A viral video on WhatsApp claims that Maggi instant noodles are manufactured from flour that has rotted for four to five days as well as pig marrow.

News_Title: People from Hunza are not cancer-free due to apricot seeds
News_Text: A viral video posted on Instagram and Facebook claims the people from Hunza never get cancer, the average age among them used to be 160, apricot seeds can prevent cancer,, and that their broken bones heal in days, and they don’t get wrinkles.

News_Title: News claiming 72% of women smoke in Pakistan is false
News_Text: Social media posts claim that the percentage of women who smoke in Pakistan has surged to 72%, citing the Pakistan Tobacco Board (PTB) as the source.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Dubious Twitter user shares misleading information about menopause
News_Text: Women these days reach menopause by age 30.

News_Title: Claim that Bill Gates-backed meat causes cancer is false

News_Title: It did not rain worms in China

The claim adds that she has given other interviews, in which she said she is proud of how her father fought against Hindus and that she is the descendant of Indian Christians from Punjab who migrated to Pakistan. Lastly, the claim urges people not to show sympathy to Christians in Pakistan “as it is their karma to pay for their deeds”.

The photo was actually taken at Lahore High Court weeks before the clashes when Khan supporters gathered as the ex-leader appeared seeking protective bail.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Old photo of tear gas shells falsely linked to Imran Khan clashes
News_Text: A photo has been deal hundreds of times in Facebook and Twitter posts that falsely claim it shows a pile of empty tear gas canisters after Pakistani police used them against supporters of former prime minister Imran Khan when they came to arrest him at his Lahore home on March 14. Although officers did use tear gas that day a reverse image search on Google shows the photo is from a November 2020 anti-blasphemy protest in Islamabad.
Label: Fake

News_Title: federal government issued instructions to stop payment of pay and pensions
News_Text: The Ministry of Finance on Saturday rejected the reports claiming that the federal government issued instructions to stop payment of pay and pensions saying all such rumours are completely false.The clarification comes after a local English daily reported that the Accountant General of Pakistan Revenue (AGPR) was directed by the finance ministry to stop clearing all the bill of the “federal ministries/divisions and attached departments till further orders”.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Pakistan did not win the World Cup of Polo Championship 2022

News_Title: AC Karor Lal Esan’s letter regarding Pak Army solidarity march is fake
News_Text: Assistant Commissioner Karor Lal Esan issued a letter to Tehsildar Muhammad Iqbal and Naib Tehsildars Naeem Ud Din Muhammad Tahir and Baz Khan demanding an explanation for their failure to assist a rally organized to express solidarity with the Pakistan Army. The letter specified that in case of a lack of response disciplinary proceedings according to the Punjab Employees Efficiency Discipline Accountability (PEEDA) Act 2006 will begin.

It seems the video was first published by digital news organisation Top Breaking News which could not be located through a Google search or on Twitter Facebook or Youtube due to its generic name. The post was captioned “As expected General Bajwa and his family returned to their country America!”

News_Title: Pakistan Railways to restore Green Line train in January 2023
News_Text: The Green Line train running between Karachi and Islamabad has been restored. The train line which was cancelled in August 2022 following heavy rains and floods will cost restored from January 2023. The claim appears to cost based on a fake notification doing the rounds on social media.

News_Title: Imran Khan did not initiate the Mohmand Dam project in KP
News_Text: Former prime minister Imran Khan initiated the Mohmand Dam project.The idea behind the Mohmand Dam project was first initiated by the Water and Power Development Authority (WAPDA) in 1963. Japan international Cooperation Agency (JICA) conducted the project’s feasibility study in 2000. The project was further modified considering the 2008 crisis and the 2010 floods and then WAPDA entered into a mutual agreement with private companies from Australia Japan and within the country in 2017. While the PTI government did indeed revive the project it was initiated at least 50 years before Imran Khan formed the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP) government.
Label: Fake

News_Title: Viral notification allegedly released by the Cabinet Secretariat is fake

News_Title: Routine WhatsApp update shared misleadingly as breaking news
News_Text: A video claims that WhatsApp will not be operational for multiple users starting on 31 December 2022.The video is misleading as WhatsApp pulls support from different out-of-date in operation systems every year. It is nothing new and is instead presented sensationally as a “breaking news” report that may confuse users.
Label: Fake
